    2. Check for any special characters: If your username, password, or database name contain special characters, make sure they are properly URL encoded. Special characters such as @, :, /, and + should be encoded using percent-encoding.

    5.     is it "mongodb": "3.6.8", fit with "mongoose": "^5.11.15",
    1 / 1

    Yes, the MongoDB driver version "3.6.8" should be compatible with the Mongoose version "^5.11.15".

    The MongoDB driver version is responsible for the low-level communication with the MongoDB server, while Mongoose acts as an Object Data Modeling (ODM) library on top of the driver, providing a higher-level abstraction for interacting with MongoDB.

    Mongoose 5.11.x versions are designed to work with MongoDB Node.js driver 3.6.x. Therefore, using MongoDB driver version 3.6.8 should be compatible with Mongoose 5.11.15.

    Make sure to install the specified versions in your project, and ensure that there are no conflicts with other dependencies.
